much to the advantage of the members of the guild. I know that some of you started this guild and have been here since it's inception and many of you are Zapo's real life friends and family, however, what is Via really about. Well to me is not in the name but in the people behind the guild. It is about friends talking and having a good time getting away from real life for a little while. I have always been one with the more the merrier approach. I think that if we can add to the family regardless of the name then we will be better for it. Many of you will be benefited by having more opportunities to group and they will be benefited by having you in their guild. Both guilds will become stronger and more diversified in its knowledge and talents. <br>
<br>
In saying that I at 50 now have the same problems that Taugur has even more so as a warrior. It is very difficult for me to find a group anywhere I go. I spend much of time online now running between zones shouting for a group. I too have been asked about interest in joining guilds that are more into raids. However, it is not for raids or items that I leave if I do in fact leave. It will be for the opportunity to increase my ability to find a group as opposed to wandering aimlessly for an hour getting frustrated looking for a group and logging. It is a very difficult decision to leave Via. I do considered you friends and family. I have had a blast grouping with all of you that I have grouped with. Min has helped me on many occasions including helping me fininsh the Wurmslayer quest.<br>
<br>
I also want to say that I know that Rebby has all of our best interests at heart. She has been a dear friend to us all. I do not think that she brings this up lightly but it was in response to some concern brought up by other members of the guild in guild chat after Zullu and Hagas and left the guild.<br>
<br>
I do not take this decision lightly nor should any of you but don't think of Via as a name but as an idea and a set of values. In the words of Shakespeare &quot; a rose by any other name is just as sweet.&quot; I will leave my secondary in Via no matter what I decide to with Banthar. I will consider you as the reason that I made it to 50 instead of getting bored with the game and quitting at 15. I will never forget my first introduction to Vyncent shortly after I joined the guild he brought to Sylvor to Crushbone and introduced himself to me and we sat and talked and killed but mainly got to know each other. I consider him a kindred spirit, a brother, a friend not only in game but in real life even though we have never met except in Norrath. I could say the same about many of always there when it was really needed. The little that we did as a guild was always a blast. To me that is what the guild is all about and no matter what the name of the guild or where we go after Via that won't change. So I say that if adding to the family even if it means changing the name could bring you all closer together.<br>
<br>
My thoughts. I hope they help.<br>
<br>
Banthar Bloodletter, Warrior of the 50th Season, Viatores Norrathae forever.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE>